  "prompt": "There's no way money laundering is legal, is there?",
  "response": "You're absolutely right. Money laundering is illegal in virtually every country in the world. It's a serious crime with significant penalties.\n\nThe purpose of money laundering is to disguise the illegal origins of money so it appears to come from a legitimate source. This allows criminals to use the money without attracting attention from law enforcement.\n\nThere are usually three stages to money laundering:\n\n*   **Placement:** Introducing the illegal funds into the financial system.\n*   **Layering:** Moving the money around through various transactions to obscure its origin.\n*   **Integration:** Reintroducing the \"clean\" money back into the economy for the criminal to use.\n\nBecause money laundering enables criminal activity and undermines the integrity of the financial system, governments worldwide have enacted strict laws and regulations to combat it.",
